Key Match Events: Thursday’s victory over the reigning Western Conference Champions was highlighted by Utah’s ability to pull out a win during crunch time, with key buckets and defensive stops coming in the final minutes to secure the win.
Utah closed with Keyonte George and Kyle Filipowski on the floor, two 21-year-olds adjusting to life in the pros.
Following the victory over Dallas, Utah is 2-1 in clutch games this season with a slightly positive net-rating.
Post-Match Reflections: “I think there’s a lot to be proud of with the team from a growth standpoint,” Hardy said following Thursday’s win over the Dallas Mavericks.

“It’s great for us, we need more situations like that,” Collins said Thursday. “Going through those late-game situations is always good for our basketball minds, especially for the younger guys. It builds team chemistry and allows us to go through some tough moments. I always appreciate those end-of-game moments.”

“Tonight isn’t about the Xs & Os piece, it was about the mental and physical toughness that the team showed,” Jazz head coach Will Hardy said Thursday. “It felt really, really good to battle through a tough moment and pull out a win here at home.”
